LocaleData.m_text:
The transport panel is where you manage lines, depots, stops, and vehicles -- in short, everything relating to your transport network.

{b}Lines{/b}
A separate panel for each vehicle type shows your current lines and lets you create new ones. Click on any line to see its schedule and list of stops. Click “Create new” to pick the stops for a new line and set up its schedule.

{b}Depots{/b}
A list of all your depots, divided to columns based on vehicle type. Click a depot name to access the depot's window, to see a list of vehicles and lines operating from it and to buy new vehicles. If you wish to rename a depot, click it on the Transport panel and choose “Edit name”.

{b}Stops{/b}
Lists all your stops and stations. Click on a stop's name to open the stop's menu, if you wish to rename the stop.

{b}Vehicles{/b}
This displays a list of all the vehicles you own. Click to rename a vehicle or to view its condition and attributes.

{b}Map data{/b}
This displays all the data that can be shown on the map. You can filter different social groups and their activities by selecting them from the columns. When you are looking at traffic density, you can also choose the time frame you want to consider, so you can, for example, see how the traffic changes with new lines.

{b}Graphs{/b}
Under graphs you can find different graphs which show how your company is doing and what is going on in the city. In the multiplayer mode, you can also see the graphs of other players' companies, so you can compare your company to them. You can open many graphs to compare them easily, and the windows can be dragged to any place on the screen.

{b}Companies{/b}
The companies tab is very important when playing a multiplayer game. Here you can see information about your competitors, and evaluate how they are doing.

{b}Cash flow{/b}
Shows you how much money your lines make, and how much it costs to keep them running.

{b}Loans{/b}
To be able to invest in more expensive vehicle types, you might need to take on a loan. After you take a loan, you will make monthly payments to repay the bank.

{b}Employees{/b}
You can adjust the wages of your employees. Wages play an important role in your company, and on this screen you can consider how they affect your transportation system. Drivers with good wages are more likely to wait to take on all passengers, maintenance personnel work more efficiently when they are well motivated, and ticket inspectors catch more people riding without a ticket.

{b}Ticket prices{/b}
You have many types of tickets to offer your passengers. Single line fares lets passengers ride on one line for one trip. Single zone tickets allow passengers to change vehicles within one zone. Multi-zone tickets allow passengers to travel freely within a larger area, and are thus more expensive.
